title: For Sale:  WWII matching numbers Mosin-Nagant, 220 rounds of milsurp ammo and many accessories
postcontent:
A very nice condition Mosin-Nagant 91/30 with all visible numbers matching (barrel, bolt, magazine and buttstock plate) and an excellent bore.   This is a 1943 rifle that appears to have been made at the Izhevsk plant (arrow in triangle) and that also carries a hammer & sickle stamp. It does have a discreet Century import marking as well.This is in original military configuration.  The stock is in good condition for its age, showing just a few dings, as well as some flaking of the varnish used by the Soviets on their stocks. I will include 220 rounds of hard-to-find milsurp ammunition with the sale.   These are the copper washed rounds that in my opinion are far superior to the plain steel commercial rounds that can be hard to extract from Mosins.In addition, you will get many accessories with the gun and all are in excellent shape. These include a bayonet, a period-correct leather and canvas sling, an oil/solvent bottle, ammunition pouches and a canvas tool bag with all the tools.  
Face to face cash sale to MN resident. Must have PTP or PTC. I would be willing to travel (within reason - i.e. southern Metro, Rochester, Mankato) to meet a serious buyer. Reply via e-mail. I will remove this ad when sold.
